<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "What aspect ratio should I use for Instagram?", answer: "Instagram supports several aspect ratios: 1:1 (square) for traditional posts, 4:5 (portrait, recommended for feed posts as it takes up more screen space), 1.91:1 (landscape), and 9:16 (Stories and Reels). The 4:5 portrait ratio is most effective for engagement as it occupies the largest area in the feed." },
  { question: "What is the standard aspect ratio for photos?", answer: "The most common photo aspect ratios are 3:2 (standard for full-frame and APS-C cameras, matching 4x6 and 6x9 prints), 4:3 (Micro Four Thirds cameras, smartphones, and many point-and-shoots), and 16:9 (widescreen, common for video). Medium format cameras often use 4:3 or 1:1." },
  { question: "How much of my image is lost when cropping to a different aspect ratio?", answer: "The amount lost depends on how different the target ratio is from the original. Cropping a 3:2 image to 1:1 removes about 33% of the pixels. Cropping a 3:2 image to 16:9 removes about 16% of the height. This calculator shows the exact percentage retained for any combination." },
  { question: "What aspect ratio is best for printing?", answer: "Common print aspect ratios are 3:2 for 4x6 and 6x9 prints, 5:4 for 8x10 prints, 7:5 for 5x7 prints, and 4:3 for 6x8 prints. If your camera shoots 3:2 and you want an 8x10 print (5:4), you will lose some of the image during cropping." },
  { question: "How do I calculate crop dimensions for a custom ratio?", answer: "To crop to a target ratio, keep the constraining dimension (the one that limits the crop) at its full size and calculate the other dimension. If the target ratio is wider than the original, use the full width and calculate height = width / target_ratio. If narrower, use the full height and calculate width = height * target_ratio." }
]) %>

<%= calculator_schema_with_ratings(
  name: "Aspect Ratio Crop Calculator",
  description: "Calculate crop dimensions to fit a target aspect ratio from original image dimensions.",
  url: photography_aspect_ratio_crop_url,
  category: "PhotographyApplication",
  calculator_slug: "aspect-ratio-crop"
) %>

